rain and the group ka vibe. This is a guideline, not a timetable.\n\n---\n\n### 1. OPENING CIRCLE - The Exchange of Stories\n**Duration:** 90 mins | **When:** Day 1 Arrival\n**Intention:** To drop titles and meet as humans.\nInstead of \"What do you do?\" — \"What story do you carry?\"\n**Flow:**\n- Everyone sits in a circle on the floor, centre has a diya\n- One by one, place your object from home in the centre\n- Share: Why this object? What part of you does it hold?\n- No fixing, no advice, just deep listening\n- Close with a collective breath, objects stay in centre for 3 days as altar\n**Needs:** Floor cushions, diya, no phones\n\n### 2. INTUITIVE STRETCHING - Morning Ritual\n**Duration:** 60 mins daily | **When:** Every morning 7:00 AM\n**Intention:** Not a yoga class. A conversation with your body after monsoon sleep.\n**Flow:** Joint loosening \u003e Cat-cow and spinal waves \u003e Hip opening led by breath \u003e Standing flows (no Sanskrit pressure) \u003e 10 min yoga nidra in savasana while it drizzles\n**Vibe:** Barefoot on wet grass, mist in the valley\n\n### 3. INNER CHILD MEDITATION\n**Duration:** 60 mins | **When:** Day 2 Morning\n**Intention:** To meet the younger you that still waits to be heard.\n**Flow:** Body scan \u003e Visualize your childhood home / gully \u003e Meet your 7-year-old self \u003e Ask: What did you need? \u003e Reparenting dialogue \u003e Bring them back with you\n**Add:** Keep a childhood photo near if they want\n\n### 4. PAINT WITH NATURE\n**Duration:** 90 mins | **When:** Day 1 Afternoon\n**Intention:** To create without needing to be an artist.\n**Flow:** Walk and collect — leaves, mud, flowers, stones \u003e Use monsoon rainwater as your water \u003e Big khadi papers on ground \u003e No prompt, just let hands move \u003e Share creations in circle\n**Needs:** Khadi sheets, natural brushes, bowls\n\n### 5. THE LOST CHILDHOOD GAMES\n**Duration:** 2 hours | **When:** Day 2 Afternoon\n**Intention:** Joy as healing. Play as prayer.\n**Flow:** Paper boats with wishes in the stream \u003e Kho-Kho (girls vs boys classic) \u003e Gilli Danda \u003e Hide \u0026 Seek in the forest / property \u003e End with cutting mangoes + toffees\n**Rule:** No phones. No being cool. Just play like 10-year-olds.\n\n### 6. ECSTATIC DANCE\n**Duration:** 90 mins | **When:** Day 2 Sunset\n**Intention:** Move what words can't.\n**Flow:** Opening circle, eyes closed \u003e Warm-up (shake) \u003e Wave 1 - Slow, earthy \u003e Wave 2 - Wild, drums \u003e Wave 3 - Heart opening \u003e Wave 4 - Stillness \u003e Lie down in silence\n**Setup:** Outdoors if rain is light, indoors with fairy lights if heavy. No talking, no alcohol, no shoes.\n\n### 7. FIRE CEREMONY - Journaling \u0026 Letting Go\n**Duration:** 90 mins | **When:** Day 1 Night\n**Intention:** What the rain washes, the fire transforms.\n**Flow:** Journal prompts: What am I carrying that's heavy? What pattern am I ready to release? \u003e Share if called to (optional) \u003e One by one, offer paper to the fire \u003e Chant / humming \u003e Silent staring at flames\n**Needs:** Havankund, ghee, journals, pens\n\n### 8. CACAO \u0026 SINGING CIRCLE\n**Duration:** 90 mins | **When:** Day 2 Night\n**Intention:** Open the heart, find your voice.\n**Flow:** Ceremonial cacao served in silence \u003e Intention for the heart \u003e Start with hum, then chants (Kabir, Bulleh Shah, folk) \u003e Guitar / Handpan / Dholak \u003e Everyone sings, no one performs \u003e Close in hug circle\n**Needs:** Ceremonial cacao, cups, instruments\n\n### 9. HANDPAN MEDITATION\n**Duration:** 60 mins | **When:** Day 3 Sunrise / Sunset by the lake\n**Intention:** To be bathed, not entertained.\n**Flow:** Lie down around the handpan \u003e No guidance, just frequencies \u003e Let monsoon + handpan do the work \u003e Slow return\n**Best spot:** Tikkar Taal lakeside point\n\n### 10. SOUND BATH\n**Duration:** 75 mins | **When:** Day 3 Late Morning\n**Intention:** Deep nervous system reset.\n**Flow:** Full body lying down, eye mask optional \u003e Crystal bowls, chimes, rain stick, gongs \u003e Rain on roof as natural sound \u003e Integration silence\n\n### 11. CLOSING CIRCLE - The Return\n**Duration:** 90 mins | **When:** Day 3 Afternoon\n**Intention:** Not goodbye, but how do you take this home?\n**Flow:** Pick back your object from centre \u003e Share: What shifted? \u003e One word you take back \u003e Group breath, group hug \u003e Tie a thread / give a seed as memory\n\n---\n\n#### Sample 3-Day Rhythm:\n\n**Day 1: ARRIVAL \u0026 REMEMBERING**\nCheck-in \u003e Intuitive Stretching Intro \u003e Opening Circle \u003e Lunch \u003e Paint with Nature \u003e Tea \u003e Fire Ceremony \u003e Dinner \u003e Stargazing\n\n**Day 2: PLAY \u0026 RELEASE**\nIntuitive Stretching \u003e Inner Child Meditation \u003e Breakfast \u003e Lost Childhood Games \u003e Lunch \u003e Ecstatic Dance \u003e Tea \u003e Cacao \u0026 Singing Circle\n\n**Day 3: STILLNESS \u0026 RETURN**\nIntuitive Stretching at Lake \u003e Handpan Meditation \u003e Breakfast \u003e Sound Bath \u003e Closing Circle \u003e Lunch \u0026 Departure\n\nWant me to also write this as Instagram captions / WhatsApp broadcast copy with your Breathe poster?"])</script><script nonce="YTQ1NmVjNzktODAwNy00NzczLTliNDUtMWI5MTIzMGUxMzBj">self.__next_f.push([1,"a3:T13a9,"])</script><script nonce="YTQ1NmVjNzktODAwNy00NzczLTliNDUtMWI5MTIzMGUxMzBj">self.__next_f.push([1,"You can share this link directly with your team / participants. It's designed like a high-end retreat brochure.\n\n### The Complete Flow — BREATHE: Monsoon Retreat\n**7-8-9 August | Morni Hills**\n\n**Philosophy:** Nothing rigid. We breathe with the rain and the group ka vibe. This is a guideline, not a timetable.\n\n---\n\n### 1. OPENING CIRCLE - The Exchange of Stories\n**Duration:** 90 mins | **When:** Day 1 Arrival\n**Intention:** To drop titles and meet as humans.\nInstead of \"What do you do?\" — \"What story do you carry?\"\n**Flow:**\n- Everyone sits in 