NO DURATION PILLS

Sessions in order (13 total, keep description short &amp; crisp, exactly this):
01 Opening Circle — The Exchange of Stories: Instead of profession, bring one object from home that represents you. We introduce ourselves through stories.
02 Intuitive Stretching — Morning Practice: Breath-led slow unwinding. Let the body lead, not the mind.
03 Movalicious — Movement + Expression + Play: Shake, flow, soften and play — movement without needing to look good. Barefoot, breath as music.
04 Inner Child Meditation — Coming Home: Meet the child you once were with tenderness. A gentle journey inward.
05 Paint with Nature — The Monsoon as Medium: Mud, turmeric, hibiscus, rainwater. Fingers over brushes. Let rain smudge it.
06 The Lost Childhood Games — Pure Play: Paper boats, Kho Kho, Pitthu, Gilli Danda, hide &amp; seek — barefoot and loud.
07 Ecstatic Dance — Outdoors / Indoors: No choreography, no watching. Ground → chaos → release → stillness.
08 Fire Ceremony — Journaling &amp; Letting Go: Journal by lantern light. Offer to fire what you no longer wish to carry.
09 Koan — Inquiry, Zen Puzzles, Self-Reflection: Sit with an unanswerable question. Sound, silence &amp; handpan hum. Not to solve, but to soften.
10 Cacao &amp; Singing Circle — Heart-Opening Night: Bitter cacao, warm songs, folk, Kabir, mantra, open hums — find your voice.
11 Handpan Meditation — Sunset Lakeside: Handpan attuned to wind at Tikkar Tal. Be bathed, not taught.
12 Sound Bath — Deep Rest: Crystal bowls, chimes, rain on roof. Lie down and let sound do the work.
13 Closing Circle — The Return: Revisit your object — what shifted? One gift, one learning, one promise to carry home.

